		<h1>Freshworks Leave Management Policy</h1>
		<h2>1. Introduction</h2>
		<p>This Leave Management Policy outlines the procedures and
			guidelines for requesting, approving, and managing leaves for
			employees at Freshworks. The purpose of this policy is to ensure fair
			and consistent treatment of all employees while maintaining the
			company's productivity and operational needs.</p>
		<h2>2. Eligibility</h2>
		<p>All regular full-time and part-time employees are eligible to
			apply for leaves as per the provisions of this policy. Temporary and
			contract employees may be eligible for certain types of leaves based
			on their employment agreement.</p>
		<h2>3. Types of Leave</h2>
		<p>
			3.1. <b>Sick Leave:</b> Sick leave is granted to employees when they
			are unable to work due to illness or injury. The number of sick leave
			days an employee can take in a year is specified in their employment
			contract..
		</p>
		<p>
			3.2. <b>Casual Leave</b>: Casual leave is a short-term leave that
			employees can use for unforeseen situations or personal emergencies.
			It is typically of shorter duration and is not pre-planned.
		</p>
		<p>
			3.3. <b>Earned Leave:</b> Earned leave, also known as privilege leave
			or personal leave, is accrued over time and can be used for planned
			absences. The number of earned leave days an employee can take is
			based on their length of service and company policy.
		</p>
		<h2>4. Leave Request Procedure</h2>
		<p>4.1. All leave requests must be submitted through the company's
			Leave Management System or on the provided leave request form.</p>
		<p>4.2. Employees must request leaves in advance whenever
			possible, except in cases of medical emergencies or unforeseen
			circumstances.</p>
		<p>4.3. Managers or supervisors are responsible for reviewing and
			approving leave requests based on operational requirements and the
			company's workload.</p>
		<h2>5. Leave Approval</h2>
		<p>5.1. Leave requests will be approved based on the following
			criteria:</p>
		<ul>
			<li>Operational requirements.</li>
			<li>Availability of the requested leave days</li>
			<li>Employee's length of service.</li>
			<li>Fair distribution of leave days among the workforce.</li>

		</ul>
		<p>5.2. Managers should communicate the approval or denial of
			leave requests to employees in a timely manner.</p>
		<h2>6. Leave Balance</h2>
		<p>6.1. Employees can check their leave balances through the Leave
			Management System.</p>
		<p>6.2. Unused annual leave may be carried over to the next year,
			subject to a maximum carryover limit.</p>
		<h2>7. Reporting Sick Leave</h2>
		<p>7.1. Employees must notify their supervisor or manager as soon
			as possible when taking sick leave.</p>
		<p>7.2. A medical certificate may be required for extended sick
			leave (usually after 3 consecutive days of illness).</p>
		<h2>8. Return to Work</h2>
		<p>Employees returning from leave are required to report to work
			on the specified date unless an extension has been approved.</p>
		<h2>9. Abandonment of Position</h2>
		<p>Failure to return to work without proper communication or
			approval may result in abandonment of the position as per company
			policies.</p>
		<h2>10. Leave Records</h2>
		<p>Accurate and up-to-date records of all leaves taken by
			employees must be maintained by the HR department.</p>
		<h2>11. Policy Review</h2>
		<p>This Leave Management Policy will be reviewed periodically and
			updated as needed to ensure compliance with legal requirements and
			the changing needs of the organization.</p>
		<h2>12. Conclusion</h2>
		<p>This Leave Management Policy is designed to provide a
			structured framework for leave management while promoting a healthy
			work-life balance for employees. All employees are expected to
			familiarize themselves with this policy and adhere to its provisions.</p>
		<p>Freshworks strives to create a fair and supportive work
			environment and encourages open communication between employees and
			management regarding leave-related matters.</p>
		<p>This policy is effective as of 01/01/2030.</p>


